<subSubSection id="C33C65302B01FFA92EC55D6CFC7A0919" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9936BB2B01FFA92EC55D6CFC7A0919" blockId="30.[498,1542,583,1050]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="4C264D382B01FFA92EC55D6CFD500F8F" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1892" box="[498,658,626,652]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Orthostixinae">Orthostixinae</taxonomicName>
were not included in our study. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B4A2B01FFA92B3F5D6CFB3C0F8F" author="Sihvonen P &amp; Mutanen M &amp; Kaila L &amp; Brehm G &amp; Hausmann A &amp; Staude HS" box="[1032,1278,626,652]" journalOrPublisher="PLOS ONE" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="20356" part="6" refId="ref20700" refString="Sihvonen P, Mutanen M, Kaila L, Brehm G, Hausmann A, Staude HS. 2011. Comprehensive molecular sampling yields a robust phylogeny for geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae). PLOS ONE 6 (6): e 20356 DOI 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0020356." title="Comprehensive molecular sampling yields a robust phylogeny for geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae)" type="journal article" year="2011">
<emphasis id="B952EAA92B01FFA92B3F5D6CFB3C0F8F" box="[1032,1278,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="4C264D382B01FFA92B3F5D6CFBB30F8F" authority="Murillo-Ramos &amp; Brehm &amp; Sihvonen &amp; Hausmann &amp; Holm &amp; Ghanavi &amp; Õunap &amp; Truuverk &amp; Staude &amp; Friedrich &amp; Tammaru &amp; Wahlberg, 2019" authorityName="Murillo-Ramos &amp; Brehm &amp; Sihvonen &amp; Hausmann &amp; Holm &amp; Ghanavi &amp; Õunap &amp; Truuverk &amp; Staude &amp; Friedrich &amp; Tammaru &amp; Wahlberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[1032,1137,626,652]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" status="new subfamily" subFamily="Sihvonen">Sihvonen</taxonomicName>
et al. (2011)
</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
showed this subfamily as deeply embedded within 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D382B01FFA92C0B5D84FC070FB7" authorityName=", Ounap et al." authorityYear="2011" box="[828,965,666,692]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Ennominae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ennominae">Ennominae</taxonomicName>
, but unfortunately it was not represented by the type genus of the subfamily. These results agree with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB74B4A2B01FFA92BA45DDCFA900FDF" author="Holloway J." box="[1171,1362,706,732]" journalOrPublisher="Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="147 - 326" part="49" refId="ref18919" refString="Holloway J. 1996. The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae. Ennominae Malayan Nature Journal 49: 147 - 326." title="The moths of Borneo, part 9: Geometridae (incl. Orthostixini), Oenochrominae, Desmobathrinae, Geometrinae" type="journal article" year="1996">
<emphasis id="B952EAA92B01FFA92BA45DDCFA900FDF" box="[1171,1362,706,732]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Holloway (1996)</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
who examined 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D382B01FFA92EC55DF4FCED0E07" authority="Hubner, (1823)" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1823" box="[498,815,746,772]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Orthostixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952EAA92B01FFA92EC55DF4FDB20E07" box="[498,624,746,772]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Orthostixis</emphasis>
Hübner, (1823)
</taxonomicName>
and suggested the inclusion in 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D382B01FFA92B915DF4FAEF0E07" authorityName=", Ounap et al." authorityYear="2011" box="[1190,1325,746,772]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Ennominae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ennominae">Ennominae</taxonomicName>
despite the full development of hindwing vein M2, the presence of a forewing areole and the very broad base of the tympanal ansa. We sampled the species 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D382B01FFA92B615C24FA600E57" authority="(Walker, 1856)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[1110,1442,825,852]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Naxa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="textilis">
<emphasis id="B952EAA92B01FFA92B615C24FB2A0E50" box="[1110,1256,825,851]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Naxa textilis</emphasis>
(Walker, 1856)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D382B01FFA92EC55C7FFC5D0E78" authority="(Hubner, 1799)" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1799" box="[498,927,865,891]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Orthostixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribraria">
<emphasis id="B952EAA92B01FFA92EC55C7FFD1C0E78" box="[498,734,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Orthostixis cribraria</emphasis>
(Hübner, 1799)
</taxonomicName>
, but only three and one marker were successfully sequenced for these samples, respectively. We included these species in the preliminary analyses but results were so unstable that we excluded them from the final analysis. Further research including fresh material and more genetic markers are needed to investigate the position of 
<taxonomicName id="4C264D382B01FFA92D4D5B1EFCD80919" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1892" box="[634,794,1024,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Orthostixinae">Orthostixinae</taxonomicName>
conclusively.
</paragraph>
